---
// Big-picture AlphaFold2 pipeline overview, for §1.5.
//
// This is a "birds-eye" view — inputs on the left, outputs on the right,
// recycling shown as a loop from outputs back around to the Evoformer.
// Scope is intentionally different from EvoformerDiagram (which zooms into
// one block) and RecyclingDiagram (which focuses on the recycling
// mechanism). This one is just the whole pipeline at a glance, for
// readers who want to orient before the deep dive in §§2–14.
---
<figure class="af2-arch-fig">
  <svg
    viewBox="0 0 900 310"
    role="img"
    aria-label="AlphaFold2 pipeline overview: three input kinds feed an embedder, which produces the MSA and pair representations m and z; these flow through 48 Evoformer blocks with recycling, then into an 8-iteration Structure Module, which emits 3D atom coordinates plus auxiliary predictions."
  >
    <defs>
      <marker id="af2-arrow" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="7" markerHeight="7" orient="auto">
        <path d="M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z" fill="var(--fg-muted)" />
      </marker>
      <marker id="af2-arrow-accent" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="7" markerHeight="7" orient="auto">
        <path d="M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z" fill="var(--accent)" />
      </marker>
    </defs>

    {/* ----- Input column (left) ----- */}
    <g class="af2-input">
      <rect x="20" y="50" width="130" height="38" rx="5" />
      <text x="85" y="73" text-anchor="middle">Target sequence</text>
    </g>
    <g class="af2-input">
      <rect x="20" y="100" width="130" height="38" rx="5" />
      <text x="85" y="123" text-anchor="middle">MSA</text>
    </g>
    <g class="af2-input">
      <rect x="20" y="150" width="130" height="38" rx="5" />
      <text x="85" y="173" text-anchor="middle">Templates</text>
    </g>

    {/* ----- Input embedder ----- */}
    <g class="af2-box af2-box--process">
      <rect x="200" y="80" width="130" height="78" rx="5" />
      <text x="265" y="110" text-anchor="middle">Input</text>
      <text x="265" y="128" text-anchor="middle">embedder</text>
      <text x="265" y="148" text-anchor="middle" class="af2-box-sub">→ m, z</text>
    </g>

    {/* Arrows from inputs to embedder */}
    <g class="af2-arrows-in">
      <path d="M 150 69 C 175 69, 180 100, 200 100" marker-end="url(#af2-arrow)" />
      <path d="M 150 119 L 195 119" marker-end="url(#af2-arrow)" />
      <path d="M 150 169 C 175 169, 180 140, 200 140" marker-end="url(#af2-arrow)" />
    </g>

    {/* ----- Evoformer ----- */}
    <g class="af2-box af2-box--accent">
      <rect x="380" y="80" width="150" height="78" rx="5" />
      <text x="455" y="110" text-anchor="middle">Evoformer</text>
      <text x="455" y="128" text-anchor="middle" class="af2-box-sub">× 48 blocks</text>
      <text x="455" y="148" text-anchor="middle" class="af2-box-sub">§§3–8</text>
    </g>

    {/* Embedder → Evoformer */}
    <path class="af2-flow" d="M 330 119 L 375 119" marker-end="url(#af2-arrow)" />
    <text x="353" y="110" text-anchor="middle" class="af2-flow-label">m, z</text>

    {/* ----- Structure Module ----- */}
    <g class="af2-box af2-box--accent">
      <rect x="580" y="80" width="150" height="78" rx="5" />
      <text x="655" y="110" text-anchor="middle">Structure</text>
      <text x="655" y="128" text-anchor="middle">Module</text>
      <text x="655" y="148" text-anchor="middle" class="af2-box-sub">× 8 iters · §10</text>
    </g>

    {/* Evoformer → Structure Module */}
    <path class="af2-flow" d="M 530 119 L 575 119" marker-end="url(#af2-arrow)" />
    <text x="552" y="110" text-anchor="middle" class="af2-flow-label">m, z</text>

    {/* ----- Outputs (right column) ----- */}
    <g class="af2-output">
      <rect x="780" y="50" width="100" height="38" rx="5" />
      <text x="830" y="73" text-anchor="middle">3D atoms</text>
    </g>
    <g class="af2-output">
      <rect x="780" y="100" width="100" height="38" rx="5" />
      <text x="830" y="118" text-anchor="middle">pLDDT /</text>
      <text x="830" y="130" text-anchor="middle">distogram</text>
    </g>
    <g class="af2-output">
      <rect x="780" y="150" width="100" height="38" rx="5" />
      <text x="830" y="173" text-anchor="middle">PAE</text>
    </g>

    {/* Structure module → outputs */}
    <g class="af2-arrows-out">
      <path d="M 730 119 C 755 119, 760 69, 780 69" marker-end="url(#af2-arrow)" />
      <path d="M 730 119 L 778 119" marker-end="url(#af2-arrow)" />
      <path d="M 730 119 C 755 119, 760 169, 780 169" marker-end="url(#af2-arrow)" />
    </g>

    {/* ----- Recycling loop ----- */}
    <path
      class="af2-recycle"
      d="M 655 158 L 655 230 L 455 230 L 455 158"
      marker-end="url(#af2-arrow-accent)"
    />
    <text x="555" y="250" text-anchor="middle" class="af2-recycle-label">
      recycle up to 4×   ·   §9
    </text>
    <text x="555" y="265" text-anchor="middle" class="af2-recycle-sub">
      detached: m₁, z, pseudo-β coords fed back in
    </text>

    {/* ----- Legend underneath ----- */}
    <text x="20" y="298" class="af2-note">
      Five key ideas of the paper: end-to-end training, the Evoformer, Invariant Point Attention, FAPE loss, and recycling.
    </text>
  </svg>

  <figcaption>
    The full AlphaFold2 pipeline at a glance. Three input modalities
    (sequence, MSA, templates) are embedded into the
    MSA representation <em>m</em> and pair representation <em>z</em>; 48
    Evoformer blocks refine both; the Structure Module then turns <em>z</em>
    and the target row of <em>m</em> into a per-residue set of rigid frames
    and atom coordinates. Up to four recycling cycles feed outputs back as
    inputs. Section numbers in each box point to where that component is
    opened up in the annotation.
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  .af2-arch-fig {
    margin: 1.75rem 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem 0.9rem;
    background: color-mix(in oklab, var(--bg) 94%, var(--rule) 6%);
  }
  .af2-arch-fig svg {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 13px;
  }

  /* Input tiles (left column) */
  .af2-input rect {
    fill: color-mix(in oklab, var(--rule) 25%, transparent);
    stroke: var(--rule);
    stroke-width: 1;
  }
  .af2-input text {
    fill: var(--fg);
    font-size: 12px;
  }

  /* Output tiles (right column) */
  .af2-output rect {
    fill: color-mix(in oklab, var(--rule) 25%, transparent);
    stroke: var(--rule);
    stroke-width: 1;
  }
  .af2-output text {
    fill: var(--fg);
    font-size: 12px;
  }

  /* Process boxes */
  .af2-box rect {
    stroke-width: 1;
  }
  .af2-box--process rect {
    fill: color-mix(in oklab, var(--rule) 35%, transparent);
    stroke: var(--rule);
  }
  .af2-box--accent rect {
    fill: color-mix(in oklab, var(--accent) 14%, transparent);
    stroke: var(--accent);
  }
  .af2-box text {
    fill: var(--fg);
    font-size: 13px;
  }
  .af2-box-sub {
    fill: var(--fg-muted) !important;
    font-size: 10.5px !important;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* Flow arrows */
  .af2-flow,
  .af2-arrows-in path,
  .af2-arrows-out path {
    stroke: var(--fg-muted);
    stroke-width: 1.3;
    fill: none;
  }
  .af2-flow-label {
    fill: var(--fg-muted);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10.5px;
  }

  /* Recycling arrow */
  .af2-recycle {
    stroke: var(--accent);
    stroke-width: 1.5;
    stroke-dasharray: 6 4;
    fill: none;
  }
  .af2-recycle-label {
    fill: var(--accent);
    font-size: 11.5px;
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .af2-recycle-sub {
    fill: var(--fg-muted);
    font-size: 10.5px;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .af2-note {
    fill: var(--fg-muted);
    font-size: 10.5px;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .af2-arch-fig figcaption {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    margin-top: 0.7rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .af2-arch-fig figcaption em { font-style: italic; color: var(--fg); }
</style>
